partnership between HR and the data scientist. In my case, I'm a data scientist who's in HR,

00:17:41.180 --> 00:17:46.619
but I also work closely with HR business partners and business unit leaders to try and get a good

00:17:46.619 --> 00:17:53.099
understanding of what items they think might be affecting attrition as I'm developing input

00:17:53.099 --> 00:17:59.020
from my models. But then we go into the predictive modeling techniques. So if you are an HR person and

00:17:59.020 --> 00:18:05.260
you are working with a data scientist, this is where they will get more heavily into the technical

